From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sr-0w <Sr-0w@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] smp: hotdog: force single-CPU direct boot

Force setup_max_cpus to zero immediately before secondary CPU bring-up. This
is an experimental direct-boot bypass for the hotdog SMP hang and is not a
production fix.
---
 kernel/smp.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/kernel/smp.c b/kernel/smp.c
index 56f83aa58..fe4785767 100644
--- a/kernel/smp.c
+++ b/kernel/smp.c
@@ -1001,2 +1001,3 @@ void __init smp_init(void)
 
+	setup_max_cpus = 0;
 	bringup_nonboot_cpus(setup_max_cpus);
-- 
2.53.0
